--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NVIDIA CUDA runtime — NOT bundled
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This package (com.vokra.unity) does NOT bundle NVIDIA CUDA runtime
libraries (cudart, cudnn, cublas, nvrtc, or the CUDA driver itself).

When CUDA acceleration is enabled at runtime, Vokra dynamically loads the
system-installed CUDA driver via:

  * dlopen("libcuda.so")  on Linux
  * LoadLibrary("nvcuda.dll")  on Windows

and dynamically loads the system-installed NVRTC via the equivalent
Driver API entry points. Vokra does not link against cudart_static and
does not ship any file named cudart*, cudnn*, cublas*, or nvcuda*.

This satisfies the NVIDIA CUDA EULA requirement that runtime
redistributables be "installed only in a private (non-shared) directory
location" — a constraint incompatible with Unity Asset Store / UPM
plugin distribution, which places DLLs in a shared Plugins directory.

Consumers requiring CUDA acceleration MUST install the NVIDIA CUDA
Toolkit separately per NVIDIA's terms. Absence of a system CUDA install
means the CUDA backend is unavailable; Vokra does NOT silently fall back
to CPU (FR-EX-08) — an explicit error is raised.

CI enforcement: scripts/check-unity-package-no-nvidia.sh runs on every
release, scanning Plugins/** for banned filenames and each shipped
.dll / .so / .dylib for undefined-symbol references to cudart / cudnn /
cublasLt. Any hit fails the release job.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party attributions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This package embeds the Vokra native runtime (vokra-capi cdylib), which
is written from scratch in Rust. Attributions for upstream research
weights and datasets consumed by Vokra models (Silero VAD, Whisper,
piper-plus, CAM++, etc.) are recorded in docs/license-audit.md in the
main Vokra repository.

The bundled sample (Samples~/VadAsrTts) uses MIT-licensed model weights
only. CC-BY-NC / CC-BY-NC-SA / non-commercial weights (F5-TTS,
Fish-Speech, Bark, EnCodec) are excluded from the official model zoo
per the M2-13 compliance gate.
